Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: Would you rather be rich and alone or be poor and find true love?
Answer.Your_Response:
I would rather be poor and find true love. Being poor is a situation I can overcome. I might not ever become rich, but I would have the things that really count in life: True love, caring, dedication, devotion, companionship. My husband and I would be able to find ways to survive financially. It might not be easy but it would be worth it. 

Being rich and alone would  be harder. You would begin to hate people because you would realize that people don't truly care for you, only what you can give them or do for them. 

There is a chance that being poor and having your true love wouldn't work out either. A lot of couples, who truly love each other, fight and break up over money issues. Lack of money to take care of one's loved ones can change a person's personality. How many horror stories have been on the news about a spouse that committed domestic violence, or even murder and it is said about that person that they used to be a wonderful person until losing their job or financial troubles began and they started drinking or doing drugs. 

Human beings need love and companionship. Now that is not to say I wouldn't prefer being Rich and having my True love together. We would be able to accomplish so much more in life and help others.
Answer.comments: This was interesting as I hadn't thought about this.

Input.slot0: Would you rather have live one hundred years in the future or one hundred years in the past?
Answer.Your_Response: 100 years in the past! No question, in some ways I am already trying to do so. We bought a piece of property last year and have started a farmstead. We are growing and raising our own food. We still use tech, but are trying to get back to a simpler way of life. It is the little things, that I love about it and make me want some more of the past. Nothing smells better then bread cooking in the oven, or laundry that has come fresh off the line. There is a sense of satisfaction that I don't get in my job that I do get from working our land. It's funny how some people react when I say we raise animals for food. People think it cruel, or gross, or too much work. Other think it is the most amazing thing ever!

Input.slot0: Does technology simplify life or make it more complicated?
Answer.Your_Response: It definitely does both, but overall it simplifies life.  It makes communication so much faster and convenient. Answer.Your_Response: I'm not sure what defines a sport. I believe fishing is a sport because it's competitive but I'm not sure a sport needs to be competitive to be considered a sport. Input.slot0: How fast do you read?
Answer.Your_Response: I try to absorb two books per week. Obviously it depends on the size of the book, considering I can breeze through Vonnegut's Cat's Cradle in a couple days yet spend most of that particular week delving through Stephen King's It. I'll never try to read more than two at a time though, but not for the most obvious reasons; I use a King of Hearts as a bookmark - and I only possess two of them. Maybe some day I'll buy myself another pack of cards to read a third book, but I'm content for now.

Title: Answer a Question

Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: What do you think about the organic food movement?
Answer.Your_Response: I am torn on this one. I think the certified organic movement is a crock. It is expense and cost prohibitive for most small farmers. There are an awful lot of hoops to jump through to attaint that label. Another issue I have is that people associate organic with no pesticide use and that is not the case. Big organic farms still use pesticides and practices that are not necessarily best for the environment. Pesticides that kill thousands of pollinators such as honey bees annually. I do think that people are paying more attention to what they are eating and starting to bring their business to their local farmer.

Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: What is your worst experience in a foreign country?
Answer.Your_Response: I went to India for a whole summer with my family once since my dad had to move there temporarily for work. Although looking back on it, there were parts I really enjoyed, it was definitely a huge culture shock. We didn't even go to a big city, we went to a small town in the middle of nowhere. Everybody stared at us everywhere we went, since we were the only foreigners around, which was very uncomfortable. On top of that, it was just very heartbreaking to see the way people lived there. As foreigners, people assumed we had loads of money and made us feel very unwelcome. I was only maybe 11 when I went, and some beggar actually spit on my face for not giving him money, even though I was a kid and didn't have anything on me.

Input.slot0: What is the longest plane trip you have taken?
Answer.Your_Response: Longest and worst flight of my life was a solid 24+ hours from Australia to Canada. I'm originally from Canada, but my family moved to Australia for a couple years. We flew back to go visit family in Canada, and man, was that flight brutal. I've never felt so horrible in my life as I did when I got off that plane. To make things worse, we had a long stopover in Minneapolis, so we went to the Mall of America, and walked through the room with all the rollercoasters and rides. Input.slot0: If you had to get rid of a holiday, which would you get rid of? Why?
Answer.Your_Response: I'd actually get rid of "April Fools Day."  It's not a major holiday, but it certainly is treated like one; at least by some people.  this is a holiday that most people treat as it should be treated...maybe have a little fun; treat it as it was intended.  but unfortunately there are some people who act like immature children just because it's "April Fools day."  they act like they can use the day as an excuse to act as a juvenile.  I can tell you from experience that some classmates said some very insensitive things to me, and thought it was all harmless just because it was "april fools day."  I'm 61 years old and still remember this.

Input.slot0: Where is the most beautiful place you have been?
Answer.Your_Response:
1). Top of Mt Chilhowee in Tennessee, after hiking all around the Ocoee River, went up there to watch the sunset from a rock structured gazebo. 

2). Pretty Place, Cleveland SC 
It's an outdoor chapel built on side of a mountain. Very special place to me that I just like to go there when nobody is there, be still, listen. 

3). Tulum Ruins of the Maya.., just totally stunning! 

4). Lake Jocassee, Salem SC 
Cold mountain lake fed by 3 rivers. Water is over 300 feet deep in some places, crystal clear all the way to the bottom, the rock formations underneath the surface just unbelievable. Surrounded by blue mountains, waterfalls galore, and has the whitest sandy beaches. The preserve around it has 80 species of plants that grow there and nowhere else on the planet. Is my favorite place on earth.

Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: Have you ever saved an animals life? How about a persons life?
Answer.Your_Response: Once my dad and I were fishing in our rubber raft and a woman and her husband tipped over their canoe. The woman was wearing a heavy coat, cowboy boots and could not swim. Her husband was trying to save her and himself but he was weighed down by his own clothing and boots. I quickly untied our boat and my dad rowed as fast as he could. Luckily I was able to hang over the boat and reach as far as I could down into the water and reach the womans hair. We rowed them to shore and they were both saved. This was very hard for a 10 year old.

Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: Have you ever saved an animals life? How about a persons life?
Answer.Your_Response: I haven't ever saved an animals life, nor a humans life. However, in the moment, I thought I did save a humans life. I was leaving work at night and traveling on the West Seattle bridge. It was empty. I was driving westbound and a car on the other side was traveling eastbound. All of a sudden it started doing barrel rolls and landed right side up right next to the little cement barriers that divide the highway you know? I had came to a screeching halt, ran out and took their pulse. Called 911. Waited with them. A taxi of guys coming back from the bar also pulled over and started praying around the person. It was crazy. They barely had a pulse and weren't using a seatbelt, because they were upside down in the drivers seat. I got a call from the offer closing the investigation like a year later telling me they passed away. It was really sad. I'll never forget that moment. I wish I could've done more.

Input.slot0: Do you prefer traveling alone or with a group?
Answer.Your_Response: That is tough, because I could enjoy either one equally. I'd say, for the sake of it, that I'd prefer to travel with a group. As a female, I'd feel safer with numbers, and it would allow me to interact with adults which I don't get enough of, in my opinion. Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: Do you prefer traveling alone or with a group?
Answer.Your_Response: I don't like groups; it's just my personality. the group would have to be very small for be to be in it.  On the other hand, traveling alone wouldn't be ideal either because it could get very frustrating.  The best option for me would be to travel with my wife; just the two of us.  But if I had to choose between being in a group, or being alone, I'd definitely travel alone.  At the age of 61, I'm tired of big-mouth arrogant "know it all" people who can ruin things in a group.  all it takes is one "bad apple" to ruin a good experience.  I'd rather go solo.

Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: What do you think of tattoos? Do you have any?
Answer.Your_Response:
I don't have any tattoos. My thinking is that they are for life, and yet my values, attitudes and body changed as I was growing up, and even though adulthood. A tattoo I selected at age 20 might not be a choice I wanted at age 40. Isn't it better to establish individuality with clothing, hair style, accessories etc? These are changeable, but a tattoo isn't. Okay, laser removal is available, but from what I hear it isn't cheap nor blemish-free.

But that is just me. I know there are others who chose a tattoo and have been happy with it.

Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: Where is the worst place you have been stuck for a long time?
Answer.Your_Response: I try to live a life without regrets and I like to see things half full than empty, so this question was at first a little difficult. Then all of a sudden I remembered my very worst working experience! It was in a family run business, where the owners were in such dire financial straights. They were in complete denial that they were in the very worst shape when they decided to hire me on. It was a couple and the wife was rarely at the business and the husband had a very bad spending habit. He decided to spend his money on me and the current lot of employees were none too happy to see me on board, since after the initial honeymoon period I was to get on board as commission. I got out of that desperate situation as quickly as I could, but it was the worst month of my career.

Title: Answer a Question
Description: answer a question or describe something or respond to a statement
Keywords: Everything! food, philosophy, science, music, sports, politics, etc.
Input.slot0: What do you think of online education?
Answer.Your_Response: As a 61-year-old, I find the concept of online education fascinating.  except for a very short free on-line course I took a few years ago, I have no experience in it.  When I went to college in the mid to late 1970s, I could never imagine a person getting educated on-line.  I would have thought that would be something that wouldn't happen for, maybe, another century.  I think it's wonderful that people can organize their life around their education; take courses from the comfort of their own home.  However, and perhaps it's because of my age, I think there's something lacking in it...I think it's more interesting when people are in the same room exchanging ideas.  I know about chat rooms but it's not the same as being physically in the same place as others.  So I think online education is good, but certainly not ideal.
